title: Spring Creek Time Trials

course:
Staging area will be on Spring Creek Road, South of Rapid City, SD
GPS Coordinates
N 43 54.749
W 103 08.04
or use address 24102 Dewey LN, Hermosa SD 57744
registration: Only day of registration will be available. Registration opens at 6:30 PM. Race will start at 7 PM. Please report to the start line at least 5 minutes before your start time.

title: Yankton Trail Crit 1
description: Sioux Falls Crit series season opener. Fun evening of racing on 1 mile loop in a park setting, great for spectators and families.
course: Yankton Trail Park roads and parking lots.
registration: Online registration open until night before the race.
notes: Good opportunity for entry-level racers, or early season training for more advanced racers. Parking and set-up area available in middle of the course if arrive before first race time. Parking also available elsewhere in park.
directions: From I-229 take Minnesota Avenue exit south, immediately turn west into Yankton Trail Park, race venue is west side of park.

title: Tour Sioux Falls
description: Tour Sioux Falls is a recreational ride culminating with a picnic at Falls Park.
course: Whatever route you want. Ride the trail system. Do a road ride with Club FAB or just show up.
registration: go to ClubFab.org. Register before June 20 to get event T-shirt along with drawstring backpack and water bottle.
directions: Falls Park is in downtown Sioux Falls.

title: Tour Sioux Falls Downtown Crit
description: The Tour Sioux Falls Downtown Crit is an afternoon event held in conjunction with Tour Sioux Falls daylong bike festival. The race is held in the heart of historic downtown Sioux Falls with lodging, restaurants and night life adjacent to the race course. Brought to you by Queen City Cycling and Spoke-n-Sport Bikes.
course: The .8 mile course is built in to the city's signature Falls Park, including a severe short climb that will challenge riders. Race is adjacent to the full day of family friendly activities of Tour Sioux Falls. http://www.mapmyride.com/routes/view/725342867
registration: Online registration is open until Midnight on June 26. Race day registration is available for additional $5.
notes: The Downtown Crit is just one element of Tour Sioux Falls, a day full of bike-related, family friendly events in the heart of beautiful downtown Sioux Falls. The event is centered at Falls Park, which is adjacent to the race course. For more information on TSF, go to TourSiouxFalls.com
directions: Falls Park is the center of the city. Follow the signs.

title: Yankton Trail Crit 2
description: Sioux Falls Crit series race 3. Fun evening of racing on 1 mile loop in a park setting, great for spectators and families.
course: Yankton Trail Park roads and parking lots.
registration: Online registration open until night before the race. On site registration opens at 5:00.
notes: Good opportunity for entry-level racers, or training for more advanced racers. Parking and set-up area available in middle of the course if arrive before first race time. Parking also available elsewhere in park.
directions: From I-229 take Minnesota Avenue exit south, immediately turn west into Yankton Trail Park, race venue is west side of park.

address.street: Big Sioux Recreation State Park - 410 Park Avenue

title: Sherman Park CX
description: Sherman Park CX brought to you by Queen City Cycling and Spoke-n-Sport bikes of Sioux Falls. The first in the series of cyclocross races for the 2015 season. Great early season event for Upper Midwest racers tuning up for Trek CXC, Oakley Night Cap, MoOCross. For more information go to Spoke-n-Sport.com or call 605-275-2453. Includes FREE kids races on a short course.
course: Technical and tight with some climbing, sand and a pavement section. Challenging and tree filled.
registration: Online registration until the night before. On-site registration increases by $5 for all classes.
notes: Note, Cat 1/2/3/4 race is not the final event. Race combinations are based on duration.
directions: From Interstate 29 take the 12th Street exit east to Kiwanis Avenue. Turn south (right) and continue to 22nd Street. Turn west (right) and venue is on your right.

title: Elmwood Forest Fat Bike expo
description: Fat bike fun on the cross course after Saturday's races. Three-inch tire width minimum. No barriers.
registration: Online until Friday night and race day at site.
notes: It's a fat bike trial, run on a CX course. Don't take yourself too seriously.
directions: Russell St. and Kiwanis Avenue, Sioux Falls.

title: Elmwood Forest CX
description: Elmwood Forest CX is the premier two-day Cyclocross festival in Sioux Falls. A fun and fast course winding through the urban forest of Elmwood Park as well as open areas for great viewing. Full slate of categories, including masters and two categories for juniors. New this year, our junior clinics sponsored by Sanford Health begin each day's racing. Cash payouts for men and women. Sponsored by Queen City Cycling, Spoke-n-Sport Bicycles and Falls Area Bicyclists.
course: Elmwood Park is the home base for cyclocross in Sioux Falls. It features a large grove of elms and old-growth cottonwoods for a spectacular scene for racing.
registration: Online registration available until 11 p.m. Oct. 23. Race day registration available at site for additional $5. Riders must show valid USA Cycling license. One day licenses will be available. Registration opens at 10 a.m. and closes 15 minutes prior to each event. No Refunds/ No free lap Online registration http://www.usacycling.org
notes: Lodging available on location at Sleep Inn Airport (sleepinn.com). Also recommended lodging within short distance at Sheraton Sioux Falls & Convention Center (starwoodhotels.com). For more information go to www.spoke-n-sport.com or call 605-275-2453
directions: Elmwood Park is located at the intersection of Russell Street and Kiwanis Avenue in Sioux Falls. From Interstate 29, take the Russell Street exit and go east approximately one mile to Kiwanis Ave. Entrance to the park is about a quarter mile south on Kiwanis Avenue.

title: Tuthill Fat Bike Expo
description: Hey, we're doing another Fat Bike ride at the end of the SD State Cross Championships.
course: Tuthill. That's all you need to know.
notes: On the CX course but we we'll make a few changes for you weenies.
directions: Tuthill Park, take the Cliff Avenue exit off I-229, go south and it's right there.

title: South Dakota State Cyclocross Championships
description: A true test of cyclocross greatness at Tuthill Park in Sioux Falls to crown our state's best. All are welcome. Medals awarded to SD residents for top three placing in division.
course: Plenty of elevation, lots of challenges, a great course.
registration: Online registration available until 11 p.m. Nov. 13. Race day registration available at site. Riders must show valid USA Cycling license. One day licenses will be available day of race for $15. Registration opens at 11 a.m. and closes 15 minutes prior to each event. No Refunds/ No free lap. Online registration http://www.usacycling.org
notes: Plenty of lodging options in the area. For more information go to www.spoke-n-sport.com or call 605-275-2453
directions: Cliff Avenue exit from Interstate 229 in Sioux Falls. South about 1/4 mile, east into Tuthill Park.
